"Overall I thought this was a nice beer and I thought it was a solid example of the style, it had pretty much all the aspects that I look for in a nice Pilsener, but I still think there's some room for improvement especially in the mouthfeel.  This beer had ok drinkability it was smooth, a little crisp, fairly creamy, slightly filling and the taste did an ok job at holding my attention, but I think one is enough for me, the flavor doesn't really make me want to come back for more and the mouthfeel holds back the drinkability.  What I like the most about this beer was the appearance, it was one damn good looking Pilsener.  What I like the least about this beer is the mouthfeel, it could use some work.  I don't think I would buy this again, but I for sure wouldn't turn it down.  I can't say I would recommend it as a great Pilsener, but it's worth a try if you like the German Pilseners.  All in all I liked this beer, but I didn't love it, it had just a couple aspects that held it back from being as good as it could be, but in the end it was still a nice example of the style and I didn't mind it.  Keep up the solid works guys, I think a little bit of work could make this a really nice beer."
