"Nice and flavorful. Expecting that Summerfest flavor but this is all together different. Definitely more complex than Summerfest. Has a nice thick hop scent up front. Head discolors after the first pour and lacing is minimal. The flavor makes up for the inadequacy of the latter. Nice and smooth with a ever so slight bitterness that is enjoyable through sequence. Going down fast. Aftertaste is wonderful. Smell translates to the flavor and doesn't have that overly sweet taste. I think I will enjoy a least three more of these before I'm through. Before you know it your on your second. Pick the traditional Pilsner glass to get the full experience of this beer. Hats off to Sierra Nevada again. Nice beer!"
