"Bottle. Clear as day. Bright golden color. Big, frothy, dense head. Lots of individual scars of laces that mark my progress down the glass. Looks exactly how it should. Smells of lager yeast, pils malt, spicy and sudsy hops. Some slightly sweet cereal grains. The flavor has some pop. A Pilsner through and through. Hops aren't overly intense yet the lend flavors of grass, soap, spice, and flower. Dry lager yeast and pils malt. Finishes with a touch of sweetness and a pale, grainy flavor. Sierra Nevada is really stressing this beer being a session beer. I agree that it is but also boasts a surprisingly full body. Perfect carbonation. A very well done Pilsner. This sixer will be recycled quite quickly."
